Very disappointing. Since I made some changes I'm not adding my rating, but this dish tasted like two forks. It was a mistake to bake 25 mins instead of fry. Panko is meant to be fried, so if you are going through the effort of breading, fry it. I eat healthfully and don't crave fried foods, but this should have been fried. The crisp-baked blobs were unsatisfying and weirdly too "fresh", even though I broiled them before breading as someone suggested. Another suggestion that didn't work: Letting the dish sit for 10-15 mins before serving. The fresh mozzarella had toughened and congealed by then. It should be served right out of the oven so the cheese is gooey. Finally, the sauce. I used tomatoes etc fresh from the farm, plus some canned organic tomatoes. The result lacked depth. Maybe roasting would help. Suggestion I wish I'd taken: Layer additional fresh basil when you assemble it. The basil got lost in the sauce. I would rename the dish I made "flab-covered undercooked egglplant with a lot of mozzarella and bland tomato sauce."

