Let me start by saying I love to cook and enjoy my time in the kitchen. That said, for the labor required for this dish, the results were distinctly mediocre. There isn't a thing wrong with the recipe, it's just a LOT of work for a meal that everyone said "Yeah, it's pretty good". Not one of four diners said "Wow, this is GREAT". I have about a dozen recipes that take 1/10 the time and get much better reactions from myself and my guests. Frying the eggplant took FOREVER and frankly, I agree with other reviewers that you go through all that effort and by the time you layer it all with sauce and bake it, you end up with mush anyhow. I will say I nearly ate all the eggplant right out of the frying pan though. That part was delicious. Think I'd be more likely to do that part and serve it up as an appetizer with an asian plum sauce than go through the whole process. Overall a decent recipe, but there are many better ones that take far less effort.

