Rating: 0
I'm Italian-American and have been making eggplant parm forever. I'd like to offer an easier preparation that actually allows the flavor of the eggplant to come through even more. Slice thickly, drizzle both sides with olive oil, sprinkle with salt and broil both sides until lightly browned. It's necessary to cut thick slices because they'll diminish greatly under the broiler. I also find that the bitter juices leech out. You can proceed with whatever recipe you prefer. I like to serve it with cappellini tossed with some of the sauce. Believe me, you won't miss the eggs, flour and breadcrumbs and you surely won't miss all the work!

